{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35a86c66-99db-4b28-851d-34122307213b","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `global.json`** — Update the SDK version:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**2. `.csproj`** — Update the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. NuGet packages** — Update any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` packages to their 11.x versions:\n```bash\ndotnet outdated        # if you have dotnet-outdated-tool\n# or manually update versions in .csproj, then:\ndotnet restore\n```\n\n**5. Build & test:**\n```bash\ndotnet build\ndotnet test\n```\n\nCheck the .NET 11 release notes / breaking changes list for any API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8671646-48c1-4b9f-a475-f4b74f21de8a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward informational question — no code to explore. I can answer directly.","outputTokens":332},"id":"1573580d-f046-4f78-8be3-9cc4e7461743","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:00:52.706Z","parentId":"87ebed2c-ac3d-4367-98d1-c71d551fba26"}
